The `forEach` method accepts a callback. The callback accepts a single parameter. The callback will repeatedly be called with each element of the array passed as the parameter.

Essentially, the callback should define what must be done with a single element of the array. `forEach` will handle the rest.

```
function logToconsole(name) {
    console.log(name);
}

names.forEach(logToconsole);
```

Generally:

```
function callback(element) { 
    // perform operation on the element 
}
```

```
array.forEach(callback);
```

