We can do this more easily if we use `summarise_if` from `dplyr`

    library(dplyr)
    MyData %&gt;%
         summarise_if(is.numeric, mean)

---

In the OP&#39;s code, it is looping through each of the columns and just `print`ing the result and not storing it.  There is also a possibility that some columns are not `numeric`.  In the below code, we pre-assign a `vector` (&#39;v1&#39;) with 0 values to store the output.  Create a logical condition with `if/else` and return the `mean` if it is `numeric` or `else` return `NA`

    v1 &lt;- numeric(length(MyData))
    for(i in seq_along(MyData)) {
        if(is.numeric(MyData[[i]])) {
            v1[i] &lt;- mean(MyData[[i]], na.rm = TRUE)
        } else {
            v1[i] &lt;- NA_real_
         }
      }

---

In `base R`, this can also be done with `sapply`

    i1 &lt;- sapply(MyData, is.numeric)
    sapply(MyData[i1], mean, na.rm = TRUE)

Or with `colMeans`

    colMeans(MyData[i], na.rm = TRUE)

