Google Map Pixels are probably not what you think in terms of real web page pixels. Maps have multiple coordinate systems, from Lat/Lng, to Tiles, to Map &quot;Pixels&quot; (relative to zoom); none of which are actual HTML pixels.

You might want to use this instead:

    var coordinates = overlay.getProjection().fromContainerPixelToLatLng(
        new google.maps.Point(x, y)
    );
(from https://stackoverflow.com/a/28037006/1060646)

